<br>
Frosty covered the Spindel camping that occurs on Bedevere, and was right on target.<br>
<br>
There is some better gear than what drops in Spindel, off of the higher level hags, but their drop rates suck serious ass compared to Spindel.<br>
<br>
On camping...yes, DAoC gives bonuses for mobs which have been up for a period of time.  I 'think' they also degrade the base experince of mobs after a long enough period of time.  They also decrease the rate at which mobs (maybe just some) spawn, if they are killed over and over.  However, if you are optimizing your experience gathering, hitting mobs that BAF (for group bonus) in controllable numbers, at reasonable cons (depends on group size/makeup), will almost always be preferable to wandering around looking for things to kill.  Experience at 41+ in DAoC is hellishly slow, unless you are constantly killing reds/purples in BAF situations.  Spin has a few of the areas that you can find these mobs in a controlled situation, Hags/Orms/etc. is another area.<br>
<br>
If they'd just put more areas to hunt, I think the camping would go down a bit in Spindel, because, while loot is important, sitting around sharing mobs that spawn less and less frequently sucks ass in a big way.  Personally, I like to do Spin in the AM before folks show up, so we can roam around the basement (or kill mobs for specific armor...fuggin chain drops), then move on to Orms/Hags in the afternoon when Spin starts to get full.<br>
<br>
Grannies in the frontier are an option, but IMHO folks exping in frontiers are just asking for a group to come along and force them to take an exp death (nother topic).<br>
<br>
Other stuff...<br>
Player made gear is still a work in process. Once 'enchantment', or whatever the comparable skill is, goes in, the need for dropped gear for stats goes away.  I'm not sure if Armorcrafting/Weaponcrafting currently offer the possiblity of making reasonable con'd gear upper40s-50, but if it's not, it probably will be, since Mythic stated something along those lines.<br>
<br>
Naele, there is actually very little interguild conflict in DAoC, at least on Bedevere.  Every once in a while a minor misunderstanding occurs, but it's few and far between.  I've never personally been KS'd and only heard of it a couple of times in the months I've been playing.  Also, groups will go out of their way to res other parties, including leaving their current camp to do so.  People also give away loot.  I've personally given away an assload of lower level Spindel loot, because noone in my guild needed it.  No charge, just a big thanks from the person who receives it.  Even reasonably high end loot (Twilight) gets given away, because at some point, banking/selling the stuff is just ridiculous.<br>
<br>
DAoC is NOT the be all, end all of MMORPGs.  It is, however a good, solid game, that has a few areas that need improvement.  A reason for RvR...needs it.  Less bugs in Keeps...needs it.  More high level content and areas to fight...definitely needs it.  But hell, it's a fun game.  People who don't even really like PvP go out and participate in big fights regardless of level.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's my 2cp, sorry I digressed from the original point of the thread, heh.<br>
<br>
